    "Although very information-rich on quasar structure, data for high magnification events have so far been scarce due to their rarity and quick evolution.",
    "Requiring almost daily cadence, these have been almost exclusively observed in a single system (the Einstein cross).",
    "In this section, we present the theoretical background that is specific to microlensing, as opposed to strong lensing in general.",
    "For an overview of the basic principles and theory of lensing we refer the reader to Saha et al. (2024).",
    "To study the lensing effect of an ensemble of compact objects in the lens plane on a background quasar, we start again by setting up the lens equation (Saha et al. 2024), but this time for many objects:"
